review_blob: Nice stout. Not a tremendous coffee flavor but noticeable. Good beer that is very sessionable.
Fantastic beer. Tastes like breakfast in a glass! Aroma was boozy when cold but was nothing but maple, coffee, and pancakes after it warmed. Taste was same with a crazy amount of body. Delicious!
This beer had great flavor mouthfeel but the habanero peppers just made it finish a bit too hot for me. Would love it with less pepper heat.

Bottle from 2014 Batch of 13.8% alcohol. Appearance is black, thick, oily. Smell is of bourbon, roast, chocolate, but mostly bourbon. Taste is a blast of bourbon alcohol that transitions into a delicious chocolate, roasted stout. This bottle tasted less boozy than the previous times Ive had it on tap this year. I dont know if its this particular batch that tastes smoother than the other which was 14.4% ABV but it sure seemed so. If youre not a huge fan of bourbon barrel beers steer clear because this brings the barrel front and center. Delicious!

Bottle- release #19. Pours pitch black with little head. Aroma is of chocolate, coffee and a hint of whiskey. Very coffee forward, followed by more coffee/espresso and chocolate, with the whiskey coming in at the tail end. Thick mouth feel with a slight waxiness left after swallowing. Good beer but a touch less coffee might let more of the whiskey/oak flavors through and it would be phenomenal. Perhaps a couple more years in the cellar will tone the coffee down and round it out more.
tastes delicious! big mouth feel, sweet bourbon, vanilla, and maple flavors. Booze was readily apparent and warming. I now understand the high ratings for this beer, its quite tasty and original.
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series # 2: CBS (Canadian Breakfast Stout)

review_blob: Pours inky black out of the bottle with a 1/4" of frothy foam on top. Smells of coffee and roasted malt. tastes primarily of coffee (go figure) with hints of chocolate, with some hop flavor. As flavor fades the mouth is overtaken by coffee bitterness. overall a good beer- a bit thin for my liking but then it probably would have been a stout.
beer_name: Tyranena BGW The Devil Made Me Do It

review_blob: On tap at brewery. Aroma of Spicy hops and malt. Hoppier than I expected but smooth and tasty. Tastes like an Octoberfest and lager combined. Highly carbonated and refreshing. I would drink a liter of this anytime.

On tap in snifter glass. Pitch black with little head, good body - sticks to the glass. Aroma of chocolate and bourbon. Tastes of bourbon, oak, coffee and loads of chocolate.....chocolate flavor lingers after swallowing. Alcohol is well hidden but still noticable. Warming makes the bourbon and chocolate more pronounced. Fantastic beer. Not sure if its better than BCBS though.
